                            <comment id="12844981" author="svarma" created="Sat, 13 Mar 2010 23:07:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Assigns a default zookeeper client port in case it is not specified in a configuration.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12844987" author="jdcryans" created="Sat, 13 Mar 2010 23:43:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Some comments:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ZK_CFG_PROPERTY + &quot;clientPort&quot;, should be made static final&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This should really be 1 line:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
+      &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; clientPortValue = HQuorumPeer.DEFAULT_ZOOKEPER_CLIENT_PORT;
+      zkProperties.put(clientPortKey, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Integer&lt;/span&gt;.valueOf(clientPortValue))
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;assignDefaultsForMissingProperties is a bit misleading, put all the other missing properties in there if there&apos;s any. If not, don&apos;t create a new method just for that.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;No need to call Integer.valueOf on ints.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Thx for looking at this Suraj!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
